            <p>My first road block was setting up my models that will later create tables in MySQL where all the database will be stored. From there, the second challenge was querying information from each table.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="technology">
            <h4>Technology</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>- C#</li>
                <li>- ASP.Net</li>
                <li>- MySQL</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

    </div>
</section>

